8 An Act relating to insurance; providing limitations
on the amount of commissions payable to a public
9 insurance adjuster; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6224 of Title 36, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 Under any method of compensation, the total commission payable
17 to a public insurance adjuster, including expenses, direct costs, or
18 any other costs accrued by the public insurance adjuster, shall not
19 exceed ten percent (10%) of the amount of the insurance settlement
20 when adjusting for entities subject to The Governmental Tort Claims
21 Act, Section 151 et seq. of Title 51 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
